From 16e5d5b1ef72f2dc4bcf546065776c7d95ea1d8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.local>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 21:54:08 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Triple drops + Sunday teacher column

Two fixes requested from the teacher-management screen.

1. Triple drops. A 'd' slot can now hold up to three students instead of
   two. Dropping a third student on an existing double-drop extends it
   (was previously rejected with 'already paired'). New helpers
   ddLegs/ddTotalInter/ddTotalKm/ddRecomputeMetrics compute per-hop
   inter-home timing from a 'legs' array stored on the slot; legacy
   2-student drops without legs still work via a fallback read of the
   scalar 'inter'. slotDur, findDropInfo, lastPos, rmFromSched, unpair,
   the slot renderer, dispatch message builder, CSV export, and
   double-drop-gap warnings all loop over ids.length instead of hard-
   coding 2. A new per-leg 3.5km gate prevents absurd detours when
   extending. tryExtendPair is the new add-on-drop handler.

2. Sunday teacher column. The Teachers modal had static Mon/Tue/Wed/Thu
   headers, so Sunday could not be ticked even when Sunday was enabled
   in Settings. The header is now built in JS from
   SETTINGS.sundayActive + SETTINGS.thursdayActive, so the columns match
   the active days in the schedule view.
